'''Richard Boateng''' (born 10 July 1992) is a Ghanaian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[AD Alcorcón]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Accra]], Boateng made his senior debuts with [[Liberty Professionals F.C.|Liberty Professionals FC]], but moved to [[Spain]] in the 2010 summer, joining [[Granada CF]]'s [[Granada CF B|reserve team]] in the regional leagues. On 26 January 2012 he was loaned to [[Cádiz CF]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/2012/01/26/futbol/equipos/granada/1327579311.html|title=El Granada cede a Richard Boateng|trans-title=Granada loans Richard Boateng|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=26 January 2012|accessdate=25 May 2014}}</ref> but only appeared with [[Cádiz CF B|the B-side]] in [[Tercera División]].

On 27 July 2012, Boateng moved to [[CD San Roque de Lepe]] in [[Segunda División B]], also in a temporary deal;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.granadaenjuego.com/seccion/Granada-CF/pub/14399/v/b|title=Boateng y Fatau, cedidos al CD San Roque|trans-title=Boateng and Fatau, loaned to CD San Roque|publisher=Granada en Juego|language=es|date=27 July 2012|accessdate=25 May 2014}}</ref> he appeared in 36 matches (2511 minutes of action), scoring two goals, but the [[Andalusia]]ns were relegated nonetheless. Upon returning he was assigned to Granada's B-side, now also in the third division.

On 28 February 2014 Boateng played his first match as a professional, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 0–4 [[La Liga]] loss at [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/en/report/372960/report.html?soccernet=true|title=Aduriz hits hat trick|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=28 February 2014|accessdate=25 May 2014}}</ref> He spent the remainder of his spell with the B-side, however.

On 1 January 2017, after an unassuming spell at [[Aris Limassol FC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Richard-Boateng-signs-for-Cyprus-side-Aris-Limasol-451350|title=Richard Boateng signs for Cyprus side Aris Limasol|publisher=Ghana Web|date=28 June 2016|access-date=5 June 2018}}</ref> Boateng joined third-tier side [[Extremadura UD]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ghanasoccernet.com/spanish-third-tier-side-extremadura-ud-announce-richard-boateng-signing|title=Spanish third-tier side Extremadura UD announce Richard Boateng signing|publisher=Ghana SoccerNet|date=2 January 2017|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref> On 3 August, he moved to fellow league team [[UD Melilla]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://udmelilla.es/noticias/15423/|title=La U.D. Melilla confirma la llegada del ghanés Richard Boateng|trans-title=U.D. Melilla confirm the arrival of Ghanaian Richard Boateng|publisher=UD Melilla|language=es|date=3 August 2017|accessdate=24 November 2017}}</ref>

Boateng scored a career-best 14 goals for Melilla during [[2017–18 Segunda División B|his first campaign]], including braces against [[Betis Deportivo Balompié]], [[Córdoba CF B]] and former side Granada B.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lavozdeasturias.es/noticia/azulcarbayon/2018/05/30/richard-boateng/00031527686888986667303.htm|title=Richard Boateng, un llegador por inercia|trans-title=Richard Boateng, a lifter by inertia|publisher=La Voz de Asturias|language=es|date=31 May 2018|access-date=5 June 2018}}</ref> On 15 June 2018, he signed a two-year contract with [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Oviedo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lne.es/real-oviedo/2018/06/15/richard-boateng-segundo-fichaje-oviedo/2303645.html|title=Richard Boateng, segundo fichaje del Oviedo|trans-title=Richard Boateng, second signing of Oviedo|publisher=[[La Nueva España]]|language=es|date=15 June 2018|access-date=15 June 2018}}</ref>

On 28 January 2019, Boateng moved to fellow second division side [[AD Alcorcón]] on loan until June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realoviedo.es/en/new/richard-boateng-loaned-to-ad-alcorcon|title=Richard Boateng Loaned to AD Alcorcón|publisher=Real Oviedo|date=28 January 2019|accessdate=4 February 2019}}</ref> On 15 July, after featuring regularly, he signed a permanent two-year contract with the ''Alfareros''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adalcorcon.com/noticia/la-ad-alcorcon-y-richard-boateng-extienden-su-vinculacion-para-las-proximas-dos-temporadas|title=La AD Alcorcón y Richard Boateng extienden su vinculación para las próximas dos temporadas|trans-title=AD Alcorcón and Richard Boateng extend their link for the following two seasons|publisher=AD Alcorcón|language=es|date=15 July 2019|accessdate=17 July 2019}}</ref>

